block.original:
Þo`r munk blo`ta,þess munk biþja,

at a_e` viþ þikeinart la`ti;



þo`'s ho~nnum o`ti`ttviþ jo~tuns bru`þir.

block.translation:
Thor shall I honor,and this shall I ask,

That his favor truemayst thou ever find;



Though little the bridesof the giants he loves.

block.original:
Senn nu o`r so~þlumsi`gask lo~`tum

auk of jo~fraa_e`ttir do/`ma;

gumna þeiraes fra` goþum kvo~`mu

block.translation:
Now let us downfrom our saddles leap,

And talk of the raceof the heroes twain;

The men who were bornof the gods above,
